<i>Everyone in New York</i>
<i>is going to die.</i>

00:21.678 --> 00:24.978
<i>But sometimes the city tries</i>
<i>to stop that from happening.</i>

00:26.244 --> 00:30.311
<i>Many people worry about things</i>
<i>that can kill them at eye level.</i>

00:30.378 --> 00:32.812
<i>But you're probably more likely</i>
<i>to be destroyed</i>

00:32.878 --> 00:34.511
<i>by something above you.</i>

00:35.745 --> 00:37.645
<i>This is why</i>
<i>the city has installed</i>

00:37.712 --> 00:40.845
<i>a sprawling network</i>
<i>of temporary sidewalk shelters</i>

00:40.912 --> 00:43.845
<i>to protect pedestrians</i>
<i>from falling objects.</i>

00:43.912 --> 00:46.511
(CLEARS THROAT)
<i>This is called scaffolding,</i>

00:46.578 --> 00:48.945
<i>and almost everywhere</i>
<i>you look in Manhattan,</i>

00:49.011 --> 00:51.712
<i>you are guaranteed to see</i>
<i>some form of it.</i>

00:52.578 --> 00:55.144
<i>It's as common</i>
<i>as a fire hydrant...</i>

00:55.211 --> 00:57.378
<i>or a honking horn,</i>

00:57.445 --> 00:59.111
<i>but most New Yorkers</i>
<i>don't even seem to</i>

00:59.178 --> 01:00.745
<i>give it a second thought.</i>

01:00.812 --> 01:02.778
So, do you have strong thoughts
about scaffolding?

01:03.378 --> 01:04.578
No, not at the moment.

01:05.345 --> 01:08.912
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING) ♪

01:08.978 --> 01:11.545
JOHN: <i>I didn't understand why</i>
<i>there was so much of it</i>

01:11.611 --> 01:12.878
<i>in New York,</i>

01:12.945 --> 01:16.078
<i>so I went on an expedition</i>
<i>to figure out</i>

01:16.144 --> 01:19.545
