<i>this unspoiled virgin island,</i>

01:41.511 --> 01:44.712
<i>New York has been a casualty</i>
<i>to man's ravenous appetite</i>

01:44.778 --> 01:46.278
<i>for over-development.</i>

01:47.511 --> 01:51.044
<i>Once the original settlers</i>
<i>tamed the bedrock,</i>

01:51.111 --> 01:54.478
<i>the only other direction</i>
<i>to build was upwards,</i>

01:54.545 --> 01:56.011
<i>towards the heavens.</i>

01:56.078 --> 01:57.278
♪ (PIANO MUSIC STOPS) ♪

01:57.345 --> 02:00.144
<i>At this point,</i>
<i>New York has some of the oldest,</i>

02:00.211 --> 02:03.978
<i>tallest, uh, most historic</i>
<i>buildings in the country.</i>

02:04.044 --> 02:06.445
<i>But their toxic relationship</i>
<i>with gravity</i>

02:06.511 --> 02:09.244
<i>has, uh, turned them</i>
<i>into a fatal liability.</i>

02:10.445 --> 02:13.645
<i>In 1979, a young student</i>
<i>was hit by a brick</i>

02:13.712 --> 02:16.978
<i>that fell off the facade</i>
<i>of a building and killed her.</i>

02:18.178 --> 02:21.278
<i>This is the intersection</i>
<i>where it happened, right here.</i>

02:22.345 --> 02:24.244
<i>Her name was Grace Gold.</i>

02:24.311 --> 02:26.511
<i>And they renamed the street</i>
<i>after her, uh,</i>

02:26.578 --> 02:27.712
<i>a few years later.</i>

