07:48.244 --> 07:50.978
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

07:51.044 --> 07:52.978
JOHN: <i>I went to a museum</i>
<i>in Queens,</i>

07:53.044 --> 07:55.011
<i>and they had</i>
<i>an art installation</i>

07:55.078 --> 07:58.111
<i>that was entirely made</i>
<i>out of scaffolding.</i>

07:58.178 --> 08:02.645
<i>It was heavily decorated with,</i>
<i>uh, waterfalls and stuff...</i>

08:02.712 --> 08:04.978
<i>and even a bunch</i>
<i>of hammocks</i>

08:05.044 --> 08:06.511
<i>that people could relax on.</i>

08:07.511 --> 08:09.578
<i>They even paid 22 dollars each</i>

08:09.645 --> 08:12.978
<i>for the chance to admire it</i>
<i>and interact with it.</i>

08:14.178 --> 08:16.111
<i>I guess it doesn't take much</i>
<i>to transform</i>

08:16.178 --> 08:19.545
<i>such a common object</i>
<i>into something extraordinary.</i>

08:19.611 --> 08:22.311
<i>It's kind of like</i>
<i>when a superhero puts on a cape</i>

08:22.378 --> 08:26.478
<i>and for some reason, no one</i>
<i>can recognize them anymore.</i>

08:26.545 --> 08:29.545
<i>And when I left, I noticed</i>
<i>that every single building</i>

08:29.611 --> 08:32.945
<i>outside the museum had</i>
<i>scaffolding up in front of it.</i>

08:33.011 --> 08:36.178
<i>But nobody seemed to want</i>
<i>to interact with this stuff.</i>

08:37.144 --> 08:39.278
♪ (CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

08:39.345 --> 08:40.645
<i>Since the dawn of cinema,</i>

