12:17.044 --> 12:20.778
This, uh, it blocks
your view of the street.

12:20.845 --> 12:22.845
We have some
nice trees out here.

12:22.912 --> 12:24.645
You can't see the trees.

12:24.712 --> 12:27.745
We've had people drilling
outside. (IMITATES DRILL)

12:27.812 --> 12:29.111
You know...

12:29.178 --> 12:32.511
It's-- It's depressing.
It's just depressing.

12:32.578 --> 12:34.211
♪ (JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

12:34.278 --> 12:36.812
JOHN: <i>Sometimes people</i>
<i>even spontaneously snap</i>

12:36.878 --> 12:38.878
<i>and try to take it down</i>
<i>themselves.</i>

12:39.678 --> 12:41.244
<i>But if you really can't stand</i>

12:41.311 --> 12:43.011
<i>scaffolding outside</i>
<i>of your building,</i>

12:43.078 --> 12:44.912
<i>the most effective</i>
<i>removal method</i>

12:44.978 --> 12:49.244
<i>is to hop into a cab, uh,</i>
<i>put on your seat belt,</i>

12:49.311 --> 12:53.111
<i>and tell the driver</i>
<i>to plow strai-- to-- to--</i>

12:53.178 --> 12:54.878
<i>to drive directly into it.</i>

12:54.945 --> 12:58.812
<i>Um, then, they'll have to</i>
<i>take it all down.</i>

12:58.878 --> 13:02.712
<i>And everyone will thank you</i>
<i>for your service.</i>

13:02.778 --> 13:04.678
(SINGING)
<i>♪ Sandman, bring me... ♪</i>

13:04.745 --> 13:06.745
JOHN: <i>Most New Yorkers</i>
<i>will put up with anything</i>

13:06.812 --> 13:08.511
<i>as long as they know</i>
<i>it's temporary.</i>

13:08.578 --> 13:10.345
(SINGING) <i>♪ Bring me a dream ♪</i>

13:10.411 --> 13:11.945
JOHN: <i>But for some people,</i>

13:12.011 --> 13:15.244
<i>the temporary nature</i>
<i>of something can be the problem.</i>

13:15.311 --> 13:16.511
BLIND MAN:
<i>You won't know there's--</i>

13:16.578 --> 13:18.445
<i>there's a pole there</i>
<i>until you run right into it.</i>

13:19.345 --> 13:20.912
Uh, the ones I really hate

13:20.978 --> 13:24.445
is when you got poles that are,
uh, elevated mostly,

13:24.511 --> 13:26.611
um, like chest level,

13:26.678 --> 13:28.845
uh, stomach level,
or even head level,

13:28.912 --> 13:31.011
where the cane can actually...

13:31.078 --> 13:33.712
glide under-- under it
and it won't detect it.

13:33.778 --> 13:36.478
And you won't know there's
a pole there until you hit it.

13:36.545 --> 13:38.378
-You see how this one is lower?
-JOHN: Yeah.

13:38.445 --> 13:40.678
So, immediately, I would, uh,

13:40.745 --> 13:43.078
immediately try to go
around this if I feel it.

13:44.244 --> 13:45.712
Goes right underneath.

13:45.778 --> 13:46.812
Uh, yeah, it'd be great

13:46.878 --> 13:48.578
to live in a city
without scaffolding.

13:49.478 --> 13:51.945
But, um, unfortunately, uh...

13:52.945 --> 13:55.111
you know,
you work with what you got.

13:55.178 --> 13:59.345
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

14:00.611 --> 14:02.078
JOHN: <i>About a decade ago,</i>

14:02.144 --> 14:04.745
<i>I had this job where</i>
<i>I had to wake up at 4 a.m.</i>

14:04.812 --> 14:08.011
<i>and go film infomercials</i>
<i>that were broadcast live</i>

14:08.078 --> 14:10.745
<i>to local cable stations</i>
<i>around the country.</i>

14:12.345 --> 14:15.545
<i>It was right here</i>
<i>at 229 West 36th Street.</i>

14:16.345 --> 14:19.044
<i>I spent many, many cold mornings</i>

14:19.111 --> 14:21.111
<i>waiting for someone</i>
<i>to buzz me in</i>

14:21.178 --> 14:24.011
<i>so I could go</i>
<i>shoot some infomercials.</i>

14:25.311 --> 14:27.845
<i>This is one of the things</i>
<i>that I shot.</i>

14:27.912 --> 14:31.545
<i>I was instructed to film</i>
<i>the beef exactly like this,</i>

14:31.611 --> 14:33.144
<i>for ten hours straight.</i>

14:33.211 --> 14:35.778
So, they're just wonderful.
They're all the buzz right now.

14:35.845 --> 14:38.278
Sweet and savory,
just delicious.

14:38.345 --> 14:39.945
Your guests will love them,

14:40.011 --> 14:43.878
and you will totally take them
to Roast-Beef-atopia.

14:43.945 --> 14:46.211
JOHN: <i>I remember</i>
<i>after the first one I did,</i>

14:46.278 --> 14:47.978
<i>I told myself that</i>
<i>I would never return</i>

14:48.044 --> 14:49.745
<i>under any circumstances.</i>

14:50.545 --> 14:52.611
<i>But five years later,</i>

14:52.678 --> 14:55.878
<i>I was still somehow standing</i>
<i>behind the same camera,</i>

14:55.945 --> 14:58.678
<i>filming the same beef</i>
<i>the same way.</i>

14:58.745 --> 15:00.311
INFOMERCIAL HOST:
Look at all that great food,

15:00.378 --> 15:03.545
hand-trimmed to exacting
specifications... (INAUDIBLE)

15:03.611 --> 15:05.211
JOHN: <i>I was afraid</i>
<i>I wouldn't be able to</i>

15:05.278 --> 15:07.244
<i>support myself</i>
<i>without steady work,</i>

15:07.311 --> 15:10.211
<i>even though I knew in my heart</i>
<i>that I was helping to create</i>

15:10.278 --> 15:13.745
<i>some of the most grotesque</i>
<i>content on the planet.</i>

15:14.745 --> 15:17.912
♪ (TRANQUIL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:17.978 --> 15:20.978
<i>It's really easy to settle for</i>
<i>something that you don't like.</i>

15:22.178 --> 15:23.845
<i>Because if you never admit</i>

15:23.912 --> 15:26.178
<i>you're unhappy</i>
<i>with something...</i>

15:26.244 --> 15:28.712
<i>then you never have</i>
<i>to change anything.</i>

15:30.478 --> 15:33.878
<i>Most of us don't speak up</i>
<i>when we're dissatisfied...</i>

15:35.445 --> 15:38.244
<i>and then things just</i>
<i>begin to accumulate</i>

15:38.311 --> 15:42.445
<i>until you can't really</i>
<i>imagine an alternative.</i>

15:44.678 --> 15:47.678
<i>You could end a relationship</i>
<i>that offers you nothing,</i>

15:47.745 --> 15:51.011
<i>or you could just</i>
<i>stay in it indefinitely</i>

15:51.078 --> 15:54.278
<i>because it's too hard</i>
<i>to move on.</i>

15:57.345 --> 16:00.411
<i>This scaffolding has been up</i>
<i>for over 20 years.</i>

16:01.411 --> 16:04.111
<i>It's at 409 Edgecombe Avenue</i>

16:04.178 --> 16:07.378
<i>in the Sugar Hill area</i>
<i>of Harlem.</i>

16:07.445 --> 16:09.712
Yeah, it's been here
my entire life.

16:09.778 --> 16:12.311
I don't know when it was put up,

16:12.378 --> 16:14.878
when they plan on
bringing it down. It's...

16:14.945 --> 16:16.178
It's just something
that's been here.

16:16.244 --> 16:19.345
Like, I-- I know we used it
for, like, sports and games.

16:19.411 --> 16:20.912
I know I used to play,
like, manhunt,

16:20.978 --> 16:23.244
and we used to climb up this
and just run it.

16:23.311 --> 16:24.511
You know, to me, I--

16:24.578 --> 16:27.912
I've known it my whole life,
so, to me, it is a landmark.

16:27.978 --> 16:31.511
JOHN: <i>But despite whatever</i>
<i>emotional attachment you have...</i>

16:31.578 --> 16:34.278
<i>scaffolding was never designed</i>
<i>to be up for this long.</i>

16:37.478 --> 16:39.678
<i>I was walking down</i>
<i>Fifth Avenue recently,</i>

16:39.745 --> 16:43.645
<i>and I saw that a bunch of</i>
<i>scaffolding had just collapsed.</i>

16:43.712 --> 16:46.211
<i>There were broken planks</i>
<i>and bricks everywhere,</i>

16:46.278 --> 16:48.011
<i>but thankfully, nobody was hurt.</i>

16:49.778 --> 16:51.411
<i>It seemed like</i>
<i>all this old scaffolding</i>

16:51.478 --> 16:53.611
<i>was a ticking time bomb.</i>

16:53.678 --> 16:56.978
<i>But instead of figuring out</i>
<i>a way to get it down sooner,</i>

16:57.044 --> 16:58.611
<i>the only noticeable innovation</i>

16:58.678 --> 17:01.244
<i>has been to make it</i>
<i>more stylish.</i>

17:02.478 --> 17:06.211
<i>In 2009, they held a</i>
<i>scaffolding design competition,</i>

17:06.278 --> 17:08.578
<i>and this thing won.</i>

17:08.645 --> 17:10.678
♪ (TRIUMPHANT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:10.745 --> 17:12.044
<i>Not long after,</i>

17:12.111 --> 17:15.211
<i>its creamy, pearly-white pillars</i>

17:15.278 --> 17:19.078
<i>started to pop up on some of the</i>
<i>city's more genteel buildings.</i>

17:20.578 --> 17:23.445
<i>Although it may be brighter</i>
<i>and less cave-like,</i>

17:23.511 --> 17:26.578
<i>this new scaffold seems</i>
<i>a lot less customizable.</i>

17:27.511 --> 17:30.044
<i>There are fewer places</i>
<i>to hang things.</i>

17:30.111 --> 17:32.311
<i>And I can't imagine</i>
<i>an action scene</i>

17:32.378 --> 17:33.578
<i>working the same way.</i>

17:34.812 --> 17:37.978
<i>It's almost as if it wants</i>
<i>New York to be a different city,</i>

17:38.044 --> 17:40.111
<i>where it looks like</i>
<i>every building</i>

17:40.178 --> 17:41.645
<i>shops at the same store.</i>

17:42.645 --> 17:44.611
<i>And I'm not sure that</i>
<i>turning scaffolding</i>

17:44.678 --> 17:47.978
<i>into a status symbol</i>
<i>is really making us any safer.</i>

17:48.044 --> 17:49.912
♪ (MUSIC STOPS) ♪

17:49.978 --> 17:52.678
<i>Fortunately, there was</i>
<i>a scaffolding convention</i>

17:52.745 --> 17:54.912
<i>happening, uh,</i>
<i>down in New Orleans.</i>

17:54.978 --> 17:56.311
<i>So I went down there</i>

17:56.378 --> 17:58.478
<i>to see if there was</i>
<i>a solution on the horizon</i>

17:58.545 --> 18:00.078
<i>that could work for everyone.</i>

18:00.144 --> 18:02.178
♪ (TRIUMPHANT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

18:03.445 --> 18:05.078
<i>When I checked in</i>
<i>to the Sheraton,</i>

18:05.144 --> 18:06.278
<i>I could already see signs</i>

18:06.345 --> 18:09.378
<i>that the scaffolding industry</i>
<i>had invaded.</i>

18:09.445 --> 18:10.778
<i>This was supposed to be</i>
<i>the cutting edge</i>

18:10.845 --> 18:12.478
<i>of scaffold technology,</i>

18:12.545 --> 18:15.445
<i>and I was, uh,</i>
<i>I was very excited.</i>

18:15.511 --> 18:19.178
♪ (TRIUMPHANT MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

18:31.778 --> 18:34.078
-JOHN: Did you invent this?
-Yeah.

18:34.144 --> 18:36.011
JOHN:
Uh, why did you invent this?

18:36.078 --> 18:38.812
Because I had a window cleaner
fall off a building and die.

18:39.411 --> 18:40.778
JOHN: Oh.

18:40.845 --> 18:43.645
♪ (TRIUMPHANT MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

18:43.712 --> 18:45.878
WINDOW WASHER MANUFACTURER:
And we can make it 13 feet long.

18:45.945 --> 18:47.311
It's an eight-footer now,
but we--

18:47.378 --> 18:48.912
That's a small side brush,
so we can add

18:48.978 --> 18:50.778
two side brushes
and it'll clean...

18:50.845 --> 18:53.078
It'll clean almost
twice as much.

18:53.144 --> 18:54.912
♪ (TRIUMPHANT MUSIC STOPS) ♪

18:54.978 --> 18:56.011
JOHN: Wow.

18:57.378 --> 18:59.178
<i>I only talked</i>
<i>to a couple of people</i>

18:59.244 --> 19:02.111
<i>before the organizers</i>
<i>of the convention approached me</i>

19:02.178 --> 19:04.178
<i>and told me that I needed</i>
<i>to stop filming.</i>

19:04.244 --> 19:05.411
Uh, why is that?

19:06.311 --> 19:07.945
ORGANIZER 1:

19:08.011 --> 19:09.378
ORGANIZER 2: Yes.

19:09.445 --> 19:11.545
JOHN: <i>They said that there were</i>
<i>too many industry secrets here,</i>

19:11.611 --> 19:13.945
<i>and I couldn't be trusted</i>
<i>not to steal them.</i>

19:14.011 --> 19:15.478
So I can't go around--

19:15.545 --> 19:17.011
ORGANIZERS:

19:17.078 --> 19:18.111
JOHN: All right.

19:18.745 --> 19:20.445
<i>I was crushed.</i>

19:20.511 --> 19:22.278
<i>But thankfully,</i>
<i>there were a bunch of</i>

19:22.345 --> 19:24.511
<i>scaffolding people</i>
<i>hanging around outside,</i>

19:24.578 --> 19:27.345
<i>and they were fine telling me</i>
<i>all their secrets.</i>

19:27.411 --> 19:30.445
Business is good,
business is booming, uh,

19:30.511 --> 19:33.445
our s-- our sales
are increasing year over year.

19:33.511 --> 19:34.912
If you're in New York City,
you will--

19:34.978 --> 19:36.311
you will never
get away from scaffolding,

19:36.378 --> 19:37.745
-I can promise you that.
-(CHUCKLES)

19:37.812 --> 19:40.912
JOHN: Do you worry
about stuff falling on you, uh,

19:40.978 --> 19:42.678
when you walk around cities?

19:42.745 --> 19:44.845
-Oh, yes. Yes.
-Sometimes, yes.

19:44.912 --> 19:47.078
Unless my husband has done
the scaffolding,

19:47.144 --> 19:48.345
I don't worry about it.

19:48.411 --> 19:50.244
JOHN: When you see
a well-done scaffolding job,

19:50.311 --> 19:51.511
do you see beauty?

19:51.578 --> 19:52.778
-Yes.
-Yes.

19:52.845 --> 19:54.812
-And safety.
-Yes.

19:54.878 --> 19:56.345
JOHN: Can scaffolding be art?

19:56.411 --> 19:58.211
-Yes, it can. It is art.
-It is. Yes.

19:58.278 --> 19:59.311
-It is art.
-It is art.

19:59.378 --> 20:00.445
♪ (MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

20:00.511 --> 20:02.078
JOHN: <i>Walking around downtown,</i>

20:02.144 --> 20:04.678
<i>I actually didn't even see</i>
<i>any scaffolding.</i>

20:06.078 --> 20:08.912
<i>Maybe this is because all</i>
<i>the scaffolding in New Orleans</i>

20:08.978 --> 20:12.878
<i>was actually built into</i>
<i>the architecture down here.</i>

20:13.745 --> 20:16.445
<i>It was a beautiful alternative.</i>

20:16.511 --> 20:19.511
<i>Would New York be better off</i>
<i>if we had something permanent</i>

20:19.578 --> 20:22.244
<i>instead of this temporary stuff</i>
<i>being erected</i>

20:22.311 --> 20:23.912
<i>and dismantled all the time?</i>

20:25.278 --> 20:26.445
<i>Is this what it looks like</i>

20:26.511 --> 20:28.712
<i>when you finally commit</i>
<i>to something?</i>

20:30.645 --> 20:33.211
<i>The locals here were lucky</i>
<i>to live in a state of bliss</i>

20:33.278 --> 20:36.345
<i>enjoyed only by those</i>
<i>ignorant of scaffolding.</i>

20:36.411 --> 20:38.211
What are your thoughts
on scaffolding?

20:38.278 --> 20:40.978
I don't even know what that is,
I'm gonna be honest with you.

20:41.044 --> 20:43.144
JOHN: Do you ever worry about,
uh, things falling

20:43.211 --> 20:44.778
and hitting you on the head?

20:44.845 --> 20:46.712
All the time.
They got balconies up here,

20:46.778 --> 20:48.578
they got people
who would throw shit at you.

20:48.645 --> 20:49.778
I've had it happen to me.

20:49.845 --> 20:52.845
They'll see the big gold
glasses, a nice juicy buff guy.

20:52.912 --> 20:54.678
"Hey, that's a target.
Let's get him."

20:54.745 --> 20:56.545
All the time, it happens,
believe me.

20:56.611 --> 20:57.945
JOHN: Can you do a trick for me?

20:58.011 --> 21:00.111
Sure. (MUFFLED)
You wanna hold the mic?

21:00.178 --> 21:02.445
♪ (STREET MUSICIAN SINGING) ♪

21:05.378 --> 21:07.244
JOHN: <i>The only scaffolding</i>
<i>I could find anywhere</i>

21:07.311 --> 21:09.511
<i>was at the new Hard Rock Hotel,</i>

21:09.578 --> 21:12.778
<i>which was being built on</i>
<i>Canal and North Rampart Street.</i>

21:14.445 --> 21:16.878
<i>Compared to what I was used</i>
<i>to seeing in New York,</i>

21:16.945 --> 21:20.878
<i>this scaffolding looked cheap</i>
<i>and haphazardly assembled.</i>

21:20.945 --> 21:22.678
<i>And for the size</i>
<i>of the building,</i>

21:22.745 --> 21:25.011
<i>I couldn't imagine that</i>
<i>it would offer much protection</i>

21:25.078 --> 21:27.411
<i>if something were to fall</i>
<i>from way up above.</i>

21:28.978 --> 21:31.611
<i>I was stunned to see that</i>
<i>the entire side of the building</i>

21:31.678 --> 21:35.144
<i>that faced North Rampart had</i>
<i>no scaffolding set up at all.</i>

21:35.211 --> 21:36.978
<i>And for the first time</i>
<i>in my life,</i>

21:37.044 --> 21:40.011
<i>I found myself wishing for</i>
<i>a little more scaffolding.</i>

21:43.078 --> 21:44.812
<i>I'd heard there was a place</i>
<i>in the French Quarter</i>

21:44.878 --> 21:47.411
<i>that made a cocktail served</i>
<i>in a fishbowl.</i>

21:47.478 --> 21:49.244
<i>So I went looking around for it.</i>

21:50.345 --> 21:52.111
<i>And I ran into a guy</i>
<i>from the convention</i>

21:52.178 --> 21:55.578
<i>who actually bought and sold</i>
<i>scaffolding companies.</i>

21:55.645 --> 21:57.044
<i>And he wanted to talk.</i>

21:57.111 --> 21:59.378
Do you think there's such
a thing as too much scaffolding?

21:59.445 --> 22:00.778
No.

22:00.845 --> 22:03.278
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

22:04.445 --> 22:05.478
JOHN: Why not?

22:06.111 --> 22:07.411
It's where I make my living.

22:07.478 --> 22:09.211
There can never be too much
scaffolding.

22:10.278 --> 22:11.712
Roll it out.

22:11.778 --> 22:14.078
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:14.144 --> 22:16.144
JOHN: <i>The whole industry</i>
<i>seemed pretty confident</i>

22:16.211 --> 22:18.178
<i>that scaffolding</i>
<i>was here to stay</i>

22:18.244 --> 22:20.712
<i>and it would continue to grow</i>
<i>like a fungus,</i>

22:20.778 --> 22:23.745
<i>but I couldn't help but think</i>
<i>that it posed its own danger.</i>

22:25.278 --> 22:26.478
<i>I tried going to a bar</i>

22:26.545 --> 22:28.945
<i>to get away from the industry</i>
<i>for a minute,</i>

22:29.011 --> 22:30.745
<i>but even the movie</i>
<i>they had on at the pub</i>

22:30.812 --> 22:33.778
<i>was filled</i>
<i>with cartoon scaffolding.</i>

22:35.778 --> 22:37.945
<i>I even read</i>
<i>a terrifying statistic</i>

22:38.011 --> 22:39.511
<i>that scaffolding failure</i>

22:39.578 --> 22:43.044
<i>was responsible for 80 deaths</i>
<i>annually across the country.</i>

22:44.311 --> 22:46.044
<i>Maybe these people</i>
<i>in the construction industry</i>

22:46.111 --> 22:48.178
<i>weren't as careful</i>
<i>as we thought.</i>

22:50.244 --> 22:52.244
<i>And when I went back</i>
<i>to Bourbon Street,</i>

22:52.311 --> 22:55.411
<i>I saw the same guy from before</i>
<i>wandering around,</i>

22:55.478 --> 22:59.311
<i>half drunk,</i>
<i>without a care in the world...</i>

22:59.378 --> 23:02.211
<i>trying to find the right</i>
<i>strip club to go into, like...</i>

23:02.278 --> 23:06.011
<i>uh, Goldilocks tasting porridge.</i>

23:06.078 --> 23:10.678
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

23:17.912 --> 23:19.878
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC STOPS) ♪

23:21.845 --> 23:23.745
JOHN: <i>The next morning,</i>
<i>I walked down to the levee</i>

23:23.812 --> 23:25.044
<i>to clear my head.</i>

23:26.778 --> 23:29.378
<i>I guess a levee is kind of</i>
<i>like scaffolding too...</i>

23:29.445 --> 23:32.545
<i>and sometimes its failure</i>
<i>could be extremely dangerous</i>

23:32.611 --> 23:34.645
<i>for the people</i>
<i>it's designed to protect.</i>

23:36.411 --> 23:38.111
